msgid "A smart contract is a transaction protocol used to be sure that an operation, involving different stakeholders, is executed as expected."
msgstr ""

#: ../../web3-dev/smart-contracts/introduction.rst:8
#: a3a60a5146f6475db92a5a3415aa30b1
msgid "Having trust between stakeholders is not necessary, as long as each participant is trusting the transaction protocol."
msgstr ""

#: ../../web3-dev/smart-contracts/introduction.rst:10
#: efdcb19afb984ccf9d01ab7f7400efc1
msgid "By adding a programmable mechanism to the blockchain, we get such a protocol as long as the program has the following characteristics:"
msgstr ""

